  "prompt": "How can I watch the Shorty Awards on TV in the US?",
  "response": "The **Shorty Awards**, which honor the best in social media and digital content, are typically available to watch online rather than on traditional TV. However, here\u2019s how you can watch them in the US:\n\n1. **Official Website**: The Shorty Awards are often streamed live on their official website, [shortyawards.com](https://shortyawards.com). Check the site for updates on the ceremony and live stream links.\n\n2. **Social Media Platforms**: The awards may be broadcast live or posted on platforms like **YouTube**, **Facebook**, or **Twitter**. Follow the Shorty Awards\u2019 official accounts for announcements.\n\n3. **Connected TV**: If the event is streamed on YouTube or another platform, you can watch it on your smart TV by accessing the platform through your TV's app or via casting from your phone or computer.\n\n4. **News Coverage**: Some media outlets might broadcast highlights or cover the event. Check entertainment or digital media news channels like **E!**, **MTV**, or **Entertainment Tonight** for possible coverage.\n\n5. **Video Hosting Platforms**: After the event, the full ceremony or clips may be uploaded to platforms like **YouTube** or **Vimeo** for on-demand viewing.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, visit the **Shorty Awards\u2019 official website** or follow their social media accounts.",
